<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

								Schedule of Racist Events (SRE)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 05-10-2022
last updated:  05-17-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 05-17-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
This script implements the Schedule of Racist Events (SRE), a questionnaire to assess 
the racial discrimination in the lives of African Americans by Landrine & Klonoff (1996).

Reference:
Landrine, H.,& Klonoff, E. A. (1996). The Schedule of Racist Events: A measure of racist discrimination
and a study of its negative physical and mental health consequences. Journal of
Black Psychology, 22(2), 144-168.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Landrine & Klonoff (1996) describe the SRE as follows:

"The Schedule of Racist Events (SRE) is an 18-item self report inventory that assesses the frequency 
of racist discrimination (specific, stressful racist events) in the past (recent racist events) and 
in one's entire life (lifetime racist events) and  measures the extent to which this discrimination 
was evaluated (appraised) as stressful (appraised racist events)."

The items are asses on the following scale:
Select '1' = If this has NEVER happened to you
Select '2' = If this has happened ONCE IN A WHILE (less than 10% of the time)
Select '3' = If this has happened SOMETIMES (10%-25% of the time)
Select '4' = If this has happened A LOT (26%-49% of the time)
Select '5' = If this has happened MOST OF THE TIME (50%-70% of the time)
Select '6' = If this has happened ALMOST ALL THE TIME (more than 70% of the time)"

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 4 minutes to complete

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'sre.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
									Scale: 1-6
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'sre_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
								
SREscore_pastyear:				the sum of all past year responses q1-q18 (Range: 18-108) 
SREscore_lifelong:				the sum of all life responses q1-q18 (Range: 18-108) 
SREscore_stresslevel:			the sum of all stress responses q1-q17 (Range: 17-102)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:
</usermanual>

<parameters>
/q15_nword = "n_____" 			//Note by the original scale authors (p.166):
								//'The actual 'n' word, rather than 'n________' appears in the scale for item 15 
								//was removed for publication by  the editors. When reproducing and using this scale, 
								// we caution the reader to use the actual word in this item
								//because that word appeared in the scale in this study.'
								//This script uses the substitution by default.
								
</parameters>


**************************************************************************************************************
				!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
</defaults>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: data file explanations under User Manual Information at the top

***********************
raw data file
***********************

***********************
summary data file
***********************
<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed, 
expressions.SREscore_pastyear, expressions.SREscore_lifelong, expressions.SREscore_stresslevel)
</summarydata>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<expressions>
/SREscore_pastyear = radiobuttons.q1a.response + radiobuttons.q2a.response + radiobuttons.q3a.response +
radiobuttons.q4a.response + radiobuttons.q5a.response + radiobuttons.q6a.response +
radiobuttons.q7a.response + radiobuttons.q8a.response + radiobuttons.q9a.response +
radiobuttons.q10a.response + radiobuttons.q11a.response + radiobuttons.q12a.response +
radiobuttons.q13a.response + radiobuttons.q14a.response + radiobuttons.q15a.response +
radiobuttons.q16a.response + radiobuttons.q17a.response + radiobuttons.q18a.response

/SREscore_lifelong = radiobuttons.q1b.response + radiobuttons.q2b.response + radiobuttons.q3b.response +
radiobuttons.q4b.response + radiobuttons.q5b.response + radiobuttons.q6b.response +
radiobuttons.q7b.response + radiobuttons.q8b.response + radiobuttons.q9b.response +
radiobuttons.q10b.response + radiobuttons.q11b.response + radiobuttons.q12b.response +
radiobuttons.q13b.response + radiobuttons.q14b.response + radiobuttons.q15b.response +
radiobuttons.q16b.response + radiobuttons.q17b.response + radiobuttons.q18b.response

/SREscore_stresslevel = radiobuttons.q1c.response + radiobuttons.q2c.response + radiobuttons.q3c.response +
radiobuttons.q4c.response + radiobuttons.q5c.response + radiobuttons.q6c.response +
radiobuttons.q7c.response + radiobuttons.q8c.response + radiobuttons.q9c.response +
radiobuttons.q10c.response + radiobuttons.q11c.response + radiobuttons.q12c.response +
radiobuttons.q13c.response + radiobuttons.q14c.response + radiobuttons.q15c.response +
radiobuttons.q16c.response + radiobuttons.q17c.response
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are not required to be answered. To change
/required = true

//////////////////////
q1
//////////////////////

<caption q1_caption>
/ caption = "1. How many times have you been treated unfairly by <i>teachers and professors</i> because you are Black?"
</caption>

<radiobuttons q1a>
/caption = "How many times in the <u>past year</u>?"
/ options = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q1b>
/caption = "How many times in your <u>entire life</u>?"
/ options = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q1c>
/caption = "How stressful was this for you??"
/ options = ("1<br>Not at all", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6<br>Extremely")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>


